This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with lemon juice mixed with water. I refilled it last week with this lemon solution, and checked it today. It did not contain any mosquito larvae, just some congealed lemon juice and other unknown insects and gelatinous substances.

This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with sink water. I refilled it last week with sink water, and checked it today. It did not contain any mosquito larvae, just some dead ants, a dead spider, and a couple of small insects.

This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with salt water. I refilled the trap with salt water last week, and checked it today. There were no mosquito larvae in the trap, but the trap did attract pill bugs, ants, spiders, a beetle, and a cockroach.
This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with alkaline water. I refilled the trap with alkaline water last week, and checked it today and found these larvae.
This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with sink water. I left it out for a week before checking it today- there were no larvae in it.

This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with sugar water. I left it out for a week before checking it today- there were no larvae in it. Ants were crawling all over the trap, and just five minutes after I cleaned and refilled the trap then placed it back, the ants had found it once more.

This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with salt water. I left it out for a week before checking it today- there were no larvae in it. There was a live cockroach in the trap, as well as some dead spiders, pill bugs, and ants. When I went to retrieve the trap, I found a large spider web next to it. I know that some spiders eat mosquito larvae, which may have to do with the absence of larvae in my trap.

This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with lemon juice mixed with water. I left it out for a week before checking it today- there were no larvae in it. The trap was filled with silver fish- most of them were dead and not fully grown, but there were a couple of live adults that crawled out when I poured the trap's contents onto a plate.

These larvae are from a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with alkaline water. I checked the trap yesterday after it had been sitting out for a week,  and I observed the larvae more closely today. The trap contained 5 larvae yesterday, and one of them became a pupa today.
This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with sink water. It was out for a week before I checked it today. This trap has never yielded any mosquito larvae.

Comments: This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with sugar water. After leaving it in a tree for 6 days, I checked it. There were no mosquito larvae in the trap, just some large dead ants. The sugar water had fermented a bit, so I poured it out and refilled it with new suagr water. I put the trap back in the tree, and will be checking it again sometime next week.

This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with alkaline water. After leaving it in the woods off of a nature trail for 6 days, I checked it. There were no mosquito larvae in the trap. I refilled the trap with alkaline water, put it back in the woods, and will be checking it again some time next week.

This is a mosquito larvae trap that I built and filled with salt water. After leaving it in the woods off of a nature trail for 6 days, I checked it. It had been knocked over, but there was still some salt water in it. However, there were no mosquito larvae in the trap. I refilled the salt water, put the trap back (making sure it was extra secure), and will be checking it again some time next week.
